WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.750 --> 00:00:02.520
- When performing the research

00:00:02.520 --> 00:00:04.653
with my first invention, OsteoStrong,

00:00:05.560 --> 00:00:08.220
we could see that humans

00:00:08.220 --> 00:00:10.500
were seven times more powerful

00:00:10.500 --> 00:00:12.480
in impact ready positions

00:00:12.480 --> 00:00:14.580
than they were in the weaker positions.

00:00:14.580 --> 00:00:17.210
This was data that only I had.

00:00:17.210 --> 00:00:18.450
And when looking at it,

00:00:18.450 --> 00:00:20.330
I realized weightlifting

00:00:20.330 --> 00:00:23.380
is a lousy stimulus for muscle growth.

00:00:23.380 --> 00:00:25.100
We needed something better.

00:00:25.100 --> 00:00:29.100
We needed something that
had the weight change

00:00:29.100 --> 00:00:32.120
as we move through
different ranges of motion

00:00:32.120 --> 00:00:35.940
to create greater fatigue of the muscle.

00:00:35.940 --> 00:00:37.890
Let me show you what I'm talking about.

00:00:38.950 --> 00:00:40.430
As you can see,

00:00:40.430 --> 00:00:41.940
lighter forces are used

00:00:41.940 --> 00:00:44.300
at the bottom of the deadlift movement.

00:00:44.300 --> 00:00:46.080
This is where people injure,

00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:49.830
so it is beneficial to
have a lower weight here.

00:00:49.830 --> 00:00:52.280
As we move through the range of motion,

00:00:52.280 --> 00:00:56.150
the weight climbs all the
way up past 600 pounds.

00:00:56.150 --> 00:00:58.730
So this gives us the benefit

00:00:58.730 --> 00:01:00.500
of incredible loading.

00:01:00.500 --> 00:01:02.410
Loading that would be higher

00:01:02.410 --> 00:01:04.200
than what you would see

00:01:04.200 --> 00:01:06.840
in a standard fitness environment.

00:01:06.840 --> 00:01:10.760
All so that multiple
repetitions can be done

00:01:10.760 --> 00:01:12.283
and we trigger more growth.

00:01:13.120 --> 00:01:15.420
When building strength and muscle,

00:01:15.420 --> 00:01:18.230
there is no getting away from heavy.

00:01:18.230 --> 00:01:20.590
X3 allows you to safely place

00:01:20.590 --> 00:01:22.840
far heavier loads on the body,

00:01:22.840 --> 00:01:25.710
which then stimulates hormonal responses

00:01:25.710 --> 00:01:27.640
that are greater than weight training

00:01:27.640 --> 00:01:29.850
to induce more growth.

00:01:29.850 --> 00:01:31.680
You end up with a full body workout

00:01:31.680 --> 00:01:33.130
that you can do at home

00:01:33.130 --> 00:01:36.210
that will be even better
than what you get at the gym.

00:01:36.210 --> 00:01:39.343
To learn more, please visit X3bar.com.

